e diagrams for $W_{2}=0$ are presented. Two different types of charge order\nwithin $\\sqrt{3} \\times \\sqrt{3}$ unit cell can occur. At $T=0$, for $W_{2}=0$\nphase separated states are degenerated with homogeneous phases (but $T>0$\nremoves this degeneration), whereas attractive $W_2<0$ stabilizes phase\nseparation at incommensurate fillings. For $U/W_{1}<0$ and $U/W_{1}>1/2$ only\nthe phase with two different concentrations occurs (together with two different\nphase separated states occurring), whereas for small repulsive $0<U/W_{1}<1/2$\nthe other ordered phase also appears (with tree different concentrations in\nsublattices). The qualitative differences with the model considered on\nhypercubic lattices are also discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 May 2021 13:01:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-05"}
